LTIMindtree Java Developer Interview - Round 2

(Managerial) | 4 Years Exp.

As promised, sharing the Round 2 - Managerial / Techno-Managerial interview experience from one of my friends who interviewed at LTIMindtree for a Java Developer role (4 years experience).

This round focused more on project understanding, problem-solving approach, and team collaboration rather than pure theory.

• Project & Technical Discussion
Explain your current project architecture end-to-end
What exactly is your role and responsibilities?
Biggest technical challenge you faced and how you solved it
How do you handle production issues / P1 defects?
What performance improvements have you implemented?

Design & Decision Making

How would you design a scalable REST API?
How do you handle concurrent user requests?
How do you ensure application security?
Experience with microservices architecture
How do services communicate with each other?

Code Quality & Process

Experience with code reviews - what do you check?
Al use case in project like copilot for code review, test case generation.
How do you ensure clean, maintainable code?
Unit testing experience (JUnit / Mockito basics)
How do you estimate tasks and meet deadlines?

• Team & Behavioral

How do you handle conflict within the team?
Experience mentoring junior developers
Working in Agile/Scrum environment
How do you handle pressure during tight releases?

Key Insight:

Apply your technical knowledge in real projects.
Strong project clarity + ownership mindset matters more than memorizing answers.
